 from fmg alpha smi med pitt edu filip gieszczykiewicz subject re self destructing copy protection on vhs tape summary that s not what they mean organization medical informatics pittsburgh pa usa lines three five klp doe carleton ca ka lun pang writes hi folks i borrowed a vhs tape from a friend and it has a warning in the begining sayi that attempts to copy the tape will result in destroying the copy and the original i found this unbelievable as playing and recording are two differen processes however i ve never seen this tape being sold anywhere so i don t want to take the chance even it s small greetings there are three types of warnings on us tapes one a hologram is glued across the seam of the two halves of the tape the message usually reads if seal is broken you must buy this tape two the standard macrovision warning copies of this tape will be unviewable three your case extended message for the average consumer tm which states that even attempting to copy the tape will destroy the original i don t believe you can sue them for misinformation in cases like this take care p s of course three is utter bs but the average consumer tm believes it heck my mom once returned such a tape without watching it she was afraid that something might just happen filip i ll buy a vowel gieszczykiewicz best e mail fmgst pitt edu all ideas are mine but they can be yours for only zero nine nine so respond now i live for my ee major winsurfing programming sca and assorted dreams two zero zero mb drive linux has one zero zero mb and ms dos has one zero zero mb ms dos is worried